### User Service — HTTP Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:8081
### Start service: pnpm nx run user-service:serve (requires Docker infra)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8081

# Paste the accessToken returned from register/login here
@accessToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIwZWFlZGM1OS1kMjQ1LTQ3ODYtOWJlNS1iM2Y4YTQ4OTRmZmIiLCJyb2xlIjoiTElTVEVORVIiLCJpYXQiOjE3ODA5Mzk2NzcsImV4cCI6MTc4MDk0MzI3N30.bAlwaHAUgxoFiIXRCCy8rEEHDqyOF7svox4MRnSjEow
@authToken = Bearer {{accessToken}}

# Paste refresh token here after login/register
@refreshToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIwZWFlZGM1OS1kMjQ1LTQ3ODYtOWJlNS1iM2Y4YTQ4OTRmZmIiLCJpYXQiOjE3ODA5Mzk2NzcsImV4cCI6MTc4MTU0NDQ3N30.vwfKQs7lVyWtx-AjHwdMOVDBIJxiUplhqkbd04g6ahQ

# Fill in after first register/login
@myUserId = 0eaedc59-d245-4786-9be5-b3f8a4894ffb

# Another user's ID (for follow/profile tests)
@otherUserId = 98200c9e-59ff-4c9d-a116-e81998e8fbf1


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUTH — Register / Login
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [1] Register new account — copy accessToken + refreshToken + user.id to variables above
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "secret1234",
  "displayName": "Alice"
}

###

### [2] Register second user (for follow tests)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "secret1234",
  "displayName": "Bob"
}

###

### [3] Login — returns new accessToken + refreshToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "newsecret5678"
}

###

### [4] Login — wrong password → 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### [5] Login — non-existent email → 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "notfound@example.com",
  "password": "secret1234"
}

###

### [6] Register duplicate email → 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "anotherpass",
  "displayName": "Alice2"
}

###

### [7] Register — password too short → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "short@example.com",
  "password": "123",
  "displayName": "ShortPass"
}

###

### [8] Refresh access token — paste refreshToken from step [1] or [3]
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### [9] Refresh with invalid token → 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "this-is-not-a-valid-token"
}

###

### [10] Logout — revokes the refresh token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{authToken}}

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### [11] Google OAuth2 — verify Google ID token (requires real token from frontend)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/oauth2/google
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idToken": "<paste-google-id-token-here>"
}

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PROFILE — Current user (/users/me)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [12] GET my profile — requires auth
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: {{authToken}}

###

### [13] GET my profile — no token → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me

###

### [14] PATCH update displayName
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{authToken}}

{
  "displayName": "Alice Updated"
}

###

### [15] PATCH update bio only
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{authToken}}

{
  "bio": "Music lover from Hanoi 🎵"
}

###

### [16] PATCH update both displayName and bio
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{authToken}}

{
  "displayName": "Alice V2",
  "bio": "Updated bio text"
}

###

### [17] PUT change password — requires currentPassword
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me/password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{authToken}}

{
  "currentPassword": "secret1234",
  "newPassword": "newsecret5678"
}

###

### [18] PUT change password — wrong current password → 400
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me/password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{authToken}}

{
  "currentPassword": "wrongpassword",
  "newPassword": "newsecret5678"
}

###

### [19] PUT upload avatar — multipart/form-data
### Use IntelliJ HTTP Client or curl for binary upload:
### curl -X PUT http://localhost:8081/api/v1/users/me/avatar \
###   -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
###   -F "file=@/path/to/avatar.jpg"
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me/avatar
Authorization: {{authToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="avatar.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./avatar.jpg
--boundary--

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PUBLIC PROFILE — Other users (/users/{userId})
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [20] GET public profile — no auth (isFollowing = false)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{otherUserId}}

###

### [21] GET public profile — with auth (isFollowing reflects real state)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{otherUserId}}
Authorization: {{authToken}}

###

### [22] GET non-existent user → 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# FOLLOW / UNFOLLOW
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [23] Follow another user → 204
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{otherUserId}}/follow
Authorization: {{authToken}}

###

### [24] Follow same user again → 409 (duplicate constraint)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{otherUserId}}/follow
Authorization: {{authToken}}

###

### [25] Follow yourself → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{myUserId}}/follow
Authorization: {{authToken}}

###

### [26] Follow non-existent user → 404
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/follow
Authorization: {{authToken}}

###

### [27] Unfollow → 204
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{otherUserId}}/follow
Authorization: {{authToken}}

###

### [28] Unfollow again (idempotent — 204, nothing happens)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{otherUserId}}/follow
Authorization: {{authToken}}

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# FOLLOWERS / FOLLOWING lists
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [29] GET followers of a user (public, no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{otherUserId}}/followers?page=0&size=20

###

### [30] GET followers — page 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{otherUserId}}/followers?page=1&size=10

###

### [31] GET following list of a user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{myUserId}}/following?page=0&size=20

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ADMIN — User management (requires ADMIN role)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# To test admin endpoints: register a user, promote to ADMIN via DB,
# then log in again to get a token with role=ADMIN.
@adminToken = Bearer <paste-admin-jwt-here>

### [32] GET all users — paginated
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/users?page=0&size=20
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

###

### [33] GET all users — filter by role
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/users?role=ARTIST&page=0&size=20
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

###

### [34] GET all users — search by name/email
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/users?search=alice&page=0&size=20
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

###

### [35] GET all users — combined filter (role + search)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/users?role=LISTENER&search=bob&page=0&size=20
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

###

### [36] PUT promote user to ARTIST
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/users/{{myUserId}}/role
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

{
  "role": "ARTIST"
}

###

### [37] PUT promote user to ADMIN
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/users/{{myUserId}}/role
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

{
  "role": "ADMIN"
}

###

### [38] PUT invalid role value → 400
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/users/{{myUserId}}/role
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

{
  "role": "SUPERUSER"
}

###

### [39] Admin endpoint without admin role → 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/users
Authorization: {{authToken}}

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# INTERNAL — inter-service endpoints (no auth, not exposed via Gateway)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [40] GET internal user by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/internal/users/{{myUserId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### [41] GET internal user — not found → 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/internal/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Accept: application/json

###

### [42] POST batch fetch users by IDs (max 100)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/internal/users/batch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userIds": [
    "{{myUserId}}",
    "{{otherUserId}}"
  ]
}

###

### [43] POST batch — empty list → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/internal/users/batch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userIds": []
}

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ACTUATOR
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [44] Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/health
Accept: application/json

###

### [45] Prometheus metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/prometheus
Accept: text/plain

###
